  "text": "This is a pleasantly simple relationship. Kuncheva [14, Appendix 10A] also shows that is κ related to the 'disagreement' measure [CITATION_1] , which counts the number of pairs of classifiers that disagree on each example, as κ = L−1 2L dis. KW variance seems more appropriate than the Q-statistic because of these links; unlike the Q-statistic, it can be written in terms of margins, is related to the intuitive disagreement measure, and has a meaningful value even on single examples.",
